analysis: The documents in this cluster consist of executive orders related to national security and foreign policy. They cover a range of topics, including energy resources, budget management, wildlife refuges, alien property, freedom of information, intelligence activities, petroleum commerce, national security and emergency preparedness communications, arms export control, labor relations, mutual security, government contracting, promotion of arts and humanities, and actions related to Sudan and Russia. The documents delegate authority to various government officials and agencies, establish committees and councils, and set forth policies and procedures for implementing these orders.
title: National Security & Foreign Policy Directives
